Sin is never justifiable.

37:28.380 --> 37:31.584
This is why it's in me so bad for you to get this.

37:31.804 --> 37:33.186
It's never justifiable.

37:33.426 --> 37:34.828
It's always condemnable.

37:36.410 --> 37:37.891
The wages of sin is what?

37:38.212 --> 37:39.553
Life, no, death.

37:40.775 --> 37:43.058
That's why it cost Christ his own life.

37:43.358 --> 37:47.864
He had to give up himself for those that would not give up themselves.

37:47.884 --> 37:49.846
And yet, he did so willingly.

37:50.046 --> 37:51.908
And here's the crazy thing about it.

37:52.229 --> 37:56.434
There's nothing justifiable about us that would ever beg him to come in.

37:57.090 --> 37:59.773
We're not appetizing.

37:59.793 --> 38:00.894
There's nothing good about us.

38:01.515 --> 38:03.096
He can't see us and think, man, you know what?

38:03.177 --> 38:04.258
I do want to come closer to them.

38:04.278 --> 38:07.401
There's nothing good about us that would ever beg him to come close.

38:07.661 --> 38:09.183
There's nothing attractive about us.

38:09.203 --> 38:11.425
There's no beauty that would garner his attention.

38:11.626 --> 38:12.246
And yet he comes.

38:12.567 --> 38:14.769
Anyways, we have no advantage to offer him.

38:16.611 --> 38:16.931
None.

38:17.812 --> 38:18.553
He doesn't need us.

38:19.714 --> 38:20.355
He doesn't need us.

38:21.276 --> 38:22.938
So why does he do this?

38:22.958 --> 38:26.962
Why then does he not only come, why then does he take on our condemnation?

38:29.058 --> 38:29.799
Because he wants us.

38:32.363 --> 38:32.924
Why, Kylan?

38:33.465 --> 38:34.146
I don't know why.

38:35.849 --> 38:37.491
Because God chooses for that to be the case.

38:38.653 --> 38:39.975
How great is love of God of this?

38:41.858 --> 38:48.448
That Christ, he gave himself up while we were yet sinners.

38:50.892 --> 38:57.202
Fourth thing, and bear with me, but we're going to finish this.

38:58.754 --> 39:07.002
Verse eight, and they heard the sound of the Lord God walking in the garden in the cool of the day and the man and his wife, they hid themselves from the presence of the Lord God among the trees of the garden.

39:07.062 --> 39:10.865
But the Lord God, he called to the man and he said to him, where are you?

39:10.925 --> 39:13.027
And he said, I heard the sound of you in the garden.

39:13.047 --> 39:16.611
I was afraid because I was naked and I hid myself.

39:18.993 --> 39:20.614
He said, who told you that you were naked?

39:20.674 --> 39:23.637
Have you eaten of the tree which I commanded you not to eat?

39:24.618 --> 39:28.722
The man said, the woman whom you gave to be with me, she gave me fruit of the tree and I ate.

39:29.794 --> 39:32.518
And in the Lord God said to the woman, what is this that you've done?

39:33.779 --> 39:35.682
The woman said the serpent deceived me and I ate.

39:38.165 --> 39:41.450
If you want to know why things keep going wrong, you need to know the fourth thing.

39:42.431 --> 39:45.154
The fourth thing is things go wrong when we stop taking responsibility.

39:46.857 --> 39:51.843
Things go wrong when we stop taking responsibility because that is absolutely what's happening here.

39:53.686 --> 39:55.588
Adam, Eve, they just start blame shifting.

39:56.009 --> 39:56.850
Adam goes first.

39:57.410 --> 39:58.111
He blames God.

39:58.351 --> 39:59.353
It's the woman you gave me.

39:59.433 --> 39:59.994
I didn't pick her.

40:00.394 --> 40:01.175
He blames Eve.

40:01.736 --> 40:02.618
She brought me the fruit.

40:03.419 --> 40:04.080
It's Eve's turn.

40:04.420 --> 40:05.201
It wasn't my fault.

40:05.642 --> 40:06.463
The serpent deceived me.

40:06.643 --> 40:14.274
Everybody is blaming somebody, but nobody is taking responsibility, which we don't do that, do we?

40:16.518 --> 40:16.838
It's funny.

40:16.858 --> 40:25.010
I was visiting with a friend earlier today and he's like, you know, the number of conversations I'm having with people where I'm having to convince them of their sin,

40:26.658 --> 40:27.880
is just crazy to me.

40:28.901 --> 40:31.765
And you know what resonated as I heard him talking about that?

40:34.108 --> 40:39.596
Repentance does not come from a convincing of man.

40:39.716 --> 40:41.498
It comes from a conviction from God.

40:42.780 --> 40:48.107
And so if someone's having to convince you, hey, you shouldn't treat people like that, hey, you shouldn't speak to people like that.

40:48.127 --> 40:50.811
Hey, the things that you're doing with your boyfriend, girlfriend, don't really need to stop that.

40:50.831 --> 40:52.313
That's not God honoring at all.

40:52.333 --> 40:56.178
If someone's having to convince you of the things, the issue is not with them, it is with you.

40:58.594 --> 41:09.609
And more than likely, if they've come to convince you, the spirit has been knocking and you've not been listening because conviction comes before anybody tries to convince.

41:12.333 --> 41:13.574
So what's God do?

41:13.594 --> 41:20.564
When all the blame shifting starts happening, when no one's willing to actually own their sin, they're just willing to acknowledge it, what happens in this moment?

41:22.707 --> 41:26.152
Well, contrary to popular belief, he doesn't show up with a ruler in hand.

41:27.393 --> 41:27.954
Growing up,

41:29.058 --> 41:34.065
My mom, she had a paint switch and labeled on it was Kylan's attitude adjuster.

41:34.866 --> 41:37.269
God does not do that for Adam.

41:37.469 --> 41:39.132
Adam does not have an attitude adjuster.

41:39.913 --> 41:40.674
God doesn't show up.

41:40.694 --> 41:41.355
He doesn't condemn him.

41:41.375 --> 41:42.076
He doesn't rebuke him.

41:42.136 --> 41:44.258
He does not in any way execute him.

41:44.279 --> 41:47.323
He does nothing that we often think God has come to do.

41:47.383 --> 41:48.945
Instead, what does he do?

41:51.468 --> 41:55.113
He just shows up for their daily walk.

41:55.133 --> 41:58.738
And yet, where Adam and Eve.

42:00.866 --> 42:01.487
They're hiding.

42:02.528 --> 42:03.349
Why are they hiding?

42:04.630 --> 42:05.151
Hear me on this.

42:05.231 --> 42:06.412
This is really important.

42:07.173 --> 42:13.780
They are hiding because for the righteous, the presence of God is delightful.

42:15.122 --> 42:17.685
But for the wicked, the presence of God is dreadful.

42:18.766 --> 42:20.207
They are filled with a fear.

42:20.828 --> 42:22.049
They know they are wicked.

42:22.089 --> 42:23.451
They are not as they should be.

42:23.491 --> 42:25.033
They have been disobedient.

42:25.053 --> 42:28.016
And as a result, they are to be despised above all men.

42:29.157 --> 42:29.938
And yet God

42:31.202 --> 42:33.145
He didn't pull him out by the hair, found ya!

42:33.585 --> 42:34.026
Guess what?

42:34.587 --> 42:36.650
It's time to take your look and let that's not what he does.

42:38.432 --> 42:38.753
I love it.

42:40.295 --> 42:41.517
He just starts asking questions.

42:42.678 --> 42:43.640
Why does he ask questions?

42:44.461 --> 42:48.827
Is it because he's not omniscient and he doesn't know what they did, he doesn't know what happened, he doesn't know what he's supposed to do?

42:48.847 --> 42:50.610
No, God is all knowing.

42:50.670 --> 42:52.352
He knows exactly what to do in this moment.

42:54.155 --> 42:59.122
No, he does what parents do whenever they catch their kid doing something they shouldn't do.

43:01.666 --> 43:06.092
sees they're guilty and then just ask them, hey, what happened?

43:06.112 --> 43:08.014
He's trying to maintain relationship.

43:08.034 --> 43:08.535
Do you see it?

43:10.257 --> 43:19.329
God does not show up in a way where he ignores what's happened, but he does not show up in a way where he ignores what's happening to them.

43:20.510 --> 43:21.051
That's big.

43:22.493 --> 43:26.297
He does see the source of their shame, but he also sees the effect of it.

43:27.119 --> 43:29.842
And so he takes care of his kids first.

43:30.754 --> 43:32.356
He starts asking them questions.

43:32.436 --> 43:34.237
Some of the questions I think he may be asking you tonight.

43:34.257 --> 43:36.600
He asks them, hey, where are you?

43:39.462 --> 43:40.103
Where are you?

43:41.364 --> 43:48.171
He wants them to know that even, even when they're lost, he will still seek them in their hiding.

43:49.512 --> 43:50.773
He asks them, who told you?

43:51.974 --> 43:56.959
He wants them to know that even when you're misled, he'll speak to them what's true.

43:58.481 --> 43:59.762
And he asks, what have you done?

44:00.834 --> 44:05.380
Because he wants them to know that even when they're guilty, he'll still save them from their sin.

44:06.702 --> 44:10.728
Don't you see, this is big, this is what Genesis 3 is about.

44:12.290 --> 44:19.901
God's fundamental response to human failure, to your failure, is not condemnation.

44:21.383 --> 44:22.204
It is compassion.

44:23.345 --> 44:24.287
It is compassion.

44:24.908 --> 44:29.554
And I wholeheartedly believe, which is why I'm taking the time to

44:30.018 --> 44:36.169
get it out of me and give it over to you that he is asking some of you the same questions tonight.

44:36.810 --> 44:40.016
That he's looking at you and he's asking, where are you?

44:40.036 --> 44:40.517
Where are you?

44:40.537 --> 44:41.940
You're not where you're supposed to be.

44:41.980 --> 44:44.044
We're supposed to walk.

44:44.064 --> 44:45.767
We're supposed to be with one another.

44:45.787 --> 44:47.089
We're supposed to be in relationship.

44:47.109 --> 44:47.710
Where are you?

44:47.750 --> 44:49.033
You're not where you're supposed to be.

44:49.053 --> 44:52.018
But who told you that?

44:52.834 --> 44:54.316
Why are you listening to those lies?

44:54.476 --> 44:55.737
I didn't tell you that.

44:55.837 --> 44:56.738
I've told you what's true.

44:56.839 --> 45:04.888
I've declared to you that your mind, your mind, son, your mind, daughter, you're safe, you're secure, you're sealed forever in Christ Jesus, by way of the Spirit, into eternal life.

45:04.988 --> 45:05.889
I don't want you just now.

45:06.149 --> 45:07.110
I want you always.

45:08.152 --> 45:09.053
Please ask him, what have you done?

45:09.093 --> 45:10.534
What have you done?

45:10.594 --> 45:15.380
That I cannot clean, that I cannot fix, that I cannot solve.

45:16.201 --> 45:17.442
He's asking you tonight.

45:17.502 --> 45:18.283
Where are you?

45:18.704 --> 45:19.385
Who told you?

45:19.825 --> 45:20.626
What have you done?

45:22.530 --> 45:26.997
Because I, I can be right when you have been wrong.

45:28.119 --> 45:31.965
You may not take responsibility, but I can take responsibility for you.

45:33.889 --> 45:43.785
Last story, just last week, as I'm sure many of you did, and so too did people from all over the globe.

45:45.087 --> 45:49.394
I sat down to watch the opening ceremony of the Olympics.

45:49.890 --> 45:57.945
the event was amazing and towards the end of the time they do what is ceremonially true of every opening ceremony at the Olympics.

45:57.986 --> 46:00.270
They bring in the Olympic torch.

46:00.410 --> 46:06.342
I don't know if you know this about the Olympic torch, but the Olympic torch is riddled with symbolism.

46:06.402 --> 46:10.770
It is so very significant because that torch is not lit by just

46:10.850 --> 46:16.498
Any regular old flame, no one just struck a matcher, you know, pulled out the flame throw and decided to light the Olympic torch.

46:16.518 --> 46:18.460
Instead, it is lit with a different fire.

46:18.520 --> 46:20.243
It is lit with a fire from another world.

46:21.825 --> 46:24.208
It is lit with the fire from the sun.

46:25.990 --> 46:34.081
And that fire is carried from Olympia, Greece, every single game.

46:35.764 --> 46:40.530
And it travels miles, thousands of miles to reach its ultimate destination.

46:43.522 --> 46:47.687
And so as I saw them bringing the torch in, I was thinking about this moment that I was going to have with you.

46:49.750 --> 46:54.355
And I couldn't help but wonder, what happens if something goes wrong?

46:56.478 --> 46:57.819
It travels that far.

46:58.420 --> 46:59.802
Surely it's been extinguished.

46:59.922 --> 47:01.203
Surely it's been quenched.

47:01.304 --> 47:03.126
Surely it's burned out at some point.

47:03.166 --> 47:05.348
What happens in that event?

47:07.992 --> 47:08.733
You want to know what happens?

47:12.137 --> 47:13.298
There is a second flame.

47:15.458 --> 47:25.413
There is a substitute that stands in the gap that burns where the first failed to burn brightest.

47:26.935 --> 47:30.741
Friends, we have a second flame.

47:32.343 --> 47:33.805
We have the second atom.

47:34.806 --> 47:39.273
We have gone wrong, but he has stood in the gap.

47:39.293 --> 47:40.475
He has taken our place.

47:40.956 --> 47:45.362
He is from another world, but he has stepped into yours that you might know him

47:46.018 --> 47:51.045
that you might trust Him, that you might believe in Him, and you might be saved by Him.

47:51.966 --> 48:00.297
Do you know this compassionate, not condemning King, if you don't?

48:03.421 --> 48:07.367
He's asking, where are you?

48:09.570 --> 48:10.231
Because I'm here.

48:11.572 --> 48:14.396
Let me pray that you would take the invitation.

48:14.416 --> 48:15.698
God, I thank you for tonight.

48:16.130 --> 48:22.838
And thank you, God, for just the power of your word, the sufficiency of it.

48:22.858 --> 48:34.272
I'm grateful, God, that Lord, you've produced and me producing us, just this posture of heart that God says, we're not playing games anymore.

48:34.312 --> 48:39.438
The world is filled with distraction and division.

48:39.498 --> 48:40.860
This will not be a place like that.

48:40.900 --> 48:41.981
We will not be distracted.

48:42.021 --> 48:42.922
We will not be divided.

48:42.942 --> 48:44.945
God, no, we will be devoted.

48:44.985 --> 48:45.906
We will be united.

48:47.266 --> 48:50.610
And yet, God, as we claim that we know, there is only one name that unites.

48:50.630 --> 48:54.134
There is only one name that saves and it's yours.

48:54.774 --> 48:55.315
It's Jesus.

48:58.458 --> 49:08.690
O God, I pray, as we set at the beginning, in an evening that matters, won't you prove it to us?

49:10.311 --> 49:16.338
Won't you pierce the heart that is within?

49:17.090 --> 49:22.356
Pull it out and hold it forever.

49:24.178 --> 49:40.676
Christ, we thank you that you lived the life we couldn't, that you died, the death we deserve, and you rose forth, and you have made eternal life available to all people if they would place their faith in you.

49:42.338 --> 49:43.359
We sing to you now.

49:43.619 --> 49:44.600
Oh God, do we sing?

49:45.441 --> 49:46.162
It's in Christ's name.

49:46.914 --> 49:47.412
Amen.

